      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHE'S SILKY (7) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by 4.5 lengths at this track in a handy 17.40 beating Little Whacker. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings six times from 11 attempts. Well placed and can measure up. CYCLONE SEBAS (6) was midfield throughout and finished there last time when 4th (23.43) at The Gardens. Has a good record here at this journey. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. WEEKEND SCOTCH (5) failed to feature last start after being shuffled back early at this track, but prior to that won by half a length at this track (17.51) beating Fire Motto in a Mix 1/2/3 on July 1. Better than last start and can bounce back. GOLDEN SUNSET (8) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.",
